caption: Great service and yummy food! Love going when we feed the ducks.

The pizza and the service was great. The only issue was the extremely loud live music right next to the outdoor seating. Could barely hear across the table and had to shout just to have conversation. We came for a nice dinner, not a concert.

Good flavors in the food along with a strong menu and a stocked bar.  The only real knock against Pane E Vino is that they a bit pricey relative to the portions.  Otherwise you've got yourself a solid local small upscale Italian eatery overlooking Big Spring Park.

This is a great place to eat and the view of the park plus the added bonus of live music Thursday - Sunday make it even better. However, this used to be a full service restaurant and their prices reflected that, it is now an order at the counter, partial service restaurant and their prices have not changed. That needs to be addressed by the owner or management. Otherwise, it’s a wonderful pizzeria and quick-bite Italian eatery.
Pane e Vino is always a great option for a casual lunch with solid food. My favorites are the Da Vinci pizza, the chicken parm, and ham and caprese sandwich.
Nice place to relax I front Spring Park.

In town for business & have always loved the food & atmosphere but it's gone downhill. The servers no longer come to your table to take the order. I watched the cook pull his phone out & type, take his earbuds out of his ears & NEVER change his gloves. He then made my meal putting the same gloves in the tomatoes & lettuce. I sent it back. I'm very disappointed with the changes.
Delicious food and great service.
During nice weather, good al fresco dinner and wine, watching families in Big Spring Park.  Great evening!
Scrumptious meatballs. Mouth watering ravioli. In the middle of downtown Huntsville.
They have great gluten-free options.  Service is usually good, sometimes meh.

If the service at this low key bistro wasn't so superb, I would first comment on the food.  But the service is really that superb!!  As far as the tasty cuisine, everything was delicious, from the pizza with goat cheese, olive oil, mushrooms, prosciutto, pears, pecans and arugula, to the spaghetti and meatballs.  Thankfully, the food was steaming hot (not always a given - see recent Florence, AL Italian restaurant's review).  From the bread sticks to the lemon cake, everything that we ordered made our tummies happy.  Prices are reasonable and the park-like setting with an outdoor patio was unique.  We'll return when we are next in town.
Solid food, heated outdoor seating, and a bit of live entertainment. Good time!

Total disaster of a place. My wife and I used to love this place. They have completely fallen apart. Tonight we ordered $50 worth of food and came home hungry. The main dishes did not taste good and the serving sizes were so small. I would not recommend this place at all. They must have a completely different cook and food supplier than what they had two years ago. What a disappointment.
Very nice little restaurant. The food was great and the view of the park was relaxing. Will go again.
The food was really good, the place is clean, well ventilated, staff is friendly and wears masks but the manager walks around without one during a global pandemic.

I did not eat and I can say that it is a bad place, I call to reserve a table and they told me that they did not make reservations that It was the first to arrive first get a table when I arrived the place was full, finally tabla was available and I want to sit down and a worker says That it is reserved, also workers are whiteout masks and cooks with cellular without masks, it hurts that I didn't even have a chance to eat and I got a very bad impression

This place used to be great! It has clearly let itself go. Wilted greens on the appetizer, crust is like a hard cracker and more of it than the pizza. Server was rude to my child (who was not being rude.) Sad to see a loved establishment of downtown fall so hard.

I had a Georgia O'Keefe pizza and it was good. The crust was soft, yet crispy, just how I like it, but it was almost burnt. The amount of sausage was sparse, and at $15 for a small/medium pizza, I'd expect a bit more meat. I waited almost 30 minutes for my pizza that they said would be ready in 10-12 minutes. Even though I was a bit displeased, I was willing to give them another chance, until I saw they had a health rating of 89. I prefer a health score of 94 or better, 92 at the least. This shows they aren't so good at keeping everything clean and operational. Had I seen their rating before ordering, I wouldn't have eaten there.
The food was great!!!
Good food
Delicious pizza and spaghetti! Highly recommend!
Great atmosphere with incredible pizza.  I’ve had several items from the menu and they are all good.  My go to’s are the El Greco and the Clemenza  My wife loves the calzones too

I have visited this place a few times since I moved here months ago. Dining in here was   ok, servers are polite, and the food has been edible with no problem. But, today we ordered take out and were given this abomination. What is supposed to be ravioli is burnt to a crisp and inedible. I would not recommend eating here to anyone. May be a place to get a quick purple cup drink, not a full restaurant.
Some of the best italian food imo. Although I wish there was a little more spacing between some of the tables though.
Decent food, nice atmosphere
Great pizza!!
This place was okay, I had lasagna and it didn't seem fresh made. I should have had the pizza I heard that it's pretty good.

I am new to the area and was excited to try this pizza place with great reviews in an awesome location. Honestly, 2 stars for the location and view of the park--but 0 stars for the food and drinks. I think a frozen pizza would have tasted better and been a fraction of the price. I do not typically leave bad reviews but I do not understand how this place has such good ratings. Maybe I just had a fluke experience, but it was bad enough I will not be returning to find out.
Had the Spaghetti & meatballs to go ... some of the best sauce I’ve had, however serving size for $15 was nowhere near expectation as compared to cost.

This was once a favorite place of ours, however it has gone downhill. When we went to pick up our carry out, we were greeted with a bad attitude. My daughter went in to pick up our order and noticed a young blond at the counter with no mask, not being very welcoming or friendly. My daughter came back to the car, but forgot to give a tip. I went back to give the tip, and the same woman was at the counter. I noticed the same attitude my daughter described. Typically, if someone makes the effort to come back to give a tip, they would be at least thanked. No evidence of gratitude whatsoever. I did not have to go back to give that tip, and sort of wished I hadn't. When we got home, both entrees were luke warm, and the pizza was rubbery - not something we'd expect for a $48 bill (including tip).
Incredible pizza
Food was amazing and incredibly fast service. Sit outside near the pond if you can
Ridiculously good Italian with a great view. Servers are friendly too.
Pretty good Italian food but the portions are a little bit on the slack side.
Loved it

Mixed experiences here, we've had some fantastic pizza and great beer. Then on other trips, fair pizza and warm beers. I will continue to go because it's a great location and the staff is always friendly.
Delicious food with excellent views. I loved the frozen adult beverage, I can't remember what they called it....great service and wonderful views of the Big Spring Park lake.

Food was ok, beer selection was great,  and all of the staff were wearing masks.  Then the manager,  I am assuming, was walking around the whole place without her mask.  She was in the restaurant,  behind the counter,  and in the kitchen without a mask.  That tells me the sanitation is not to be trusted.

Pizzas are delicious. Not heavy laden and greasy but fresh and crispy. Orders arrived quickly and customer service was perfect. Also, we love that you pay first and can leave without having to wait for the check.
I had a pizza that was very good. Qe sat outside and it is a nice view of the duck pond.  Nice atmoshpere.
Pizza was really good and atmosphere was nice. Outdoor seating featured guy singing guitar on Sunday evening.
Pizza was excellent, and the setting by the lake was nice as well.
Very good.. great on a beautiful day

Food is pretty alright. Nothing spectacular, but pretty good. Definitely come for the atmosphere. Having a drink on the patio in the park is great. They have wine, beer and some mix drinks. About $50 for two entree's and two drinks
Waited 25 minutes at a table with no service at all. (Wasn't told if we needed to order online or anything) We ended up walking out.
Good food and atmosphere. It is not an every night kind of place because of cost but that's what makes it special. Good place to take someone and relax.
Took kids here for lunch Friday, had cheese pizza and parmesan cheese breadsticks, bland no flavor kids would not eat it! Over priced and a waste of money! Sad you call this Italian
Awesome, meal was great!!
Good pizza, pricey drinks, but good to indulge with friends or a date in a beautiful park setting.
Very nice view, friendly, good service, clean, good wines, very cozy environment, Da Vinci pizza was very good and we are Michelangelo pizza.
Location was wonderful but the food was under quality.
Beautiful place
I'm not much for thin crust pizza but this was really good.

Ive been here twice! Its lovely, Very pretty modern decor .The food quality is wonderful!! Honestly the Beast pizza ive found in Huntsville. very nice mixed drinks as well as grate price on everything.

This place has a very good location and good food. The portions are very big, so I like to order one pizza and one pasta to share between two people. I think the pizza is the best thing on the menu; the margherita especially.
Excellent food
Located right in front of the Big Spring park. Great location. Good foods, but not great.

Pan E Vino is one of the nicest, high-end pizza places I have ever ordered from. My family orders from them regularly to the point where they now know who's ordering based on what we order. It's also nice because they have several really good gluten-free crusts and their kitchen is such that my wife has never been affected (she has Celiac Disease). The staff there is wonderful and super helpful. The atmosphere is amazing and I cannot wait until after coronavirus to be able to dine there safely (I am immune compromised, so I can't chance it). That said, for those who are concerned about gluten issues, they're caprese salads do come with some sort of toasted garlic bread thing so make sure you ask them to remove that first. It's not listed that way on their menu.
To the owners: The individuals closing tonight we're beyond phenomenal, cheerful and definitely won me over as a future customer
Good food, convenient for visitors to Museum of Art.

awesome food and relaxing.

Use to be one of a kind, even in super noisy trivia nights, but since Corona the dishes are smaller and the pasta wasn't hot! Outdoor tables are not that far to have your pasta warm
Great pizza!

Great pizza with patio overlooking lakeside park. Lawn games to entertain the kids while pizza cooked. Clean restrooms.
Good food and outdoor seating with great music!
Very laid back and chill. The pizza and Italian margarita were delicious!
The food was delicious! The staff was super friendly, and the playlist was on point!
Food was good, a little odd how they have things set up to order your food though

Absolutely fantastic spot! Was greeted at front by Nicole, and taken care of by chandler with fantastic service! Pizza, salad and beer were without a doubt the best I’ve had in town. Would definitely recommend stopping in if you have the chance!

The food was fantastic and for the quality very reasonably priced. The Butternut Squash Ravioli is highly recommended, and you're committing a serious offense if you arent eating the pizza fresh. More of a casual resturaunt than the pictures on their website would probably lead you to believe, but that"s not a bad thing. Highly recommended, will be frequenting from now on.  Also any resturaunt that will play The Fifth Element and Constantine for guests is a winner in my book.

Grabbed a pizza here yesterday with some friends. Told the cashier that I had Celiac and needed to be sure that the pizza would have no gluten. I was eapecially concerned because I assumed several cooking surfaces might be shared with food that did have gluten. Not only did the pizza have no gluten, it also was one of the best tasting pizzas I've ever had. Would highly recommend.

They must have put something in this pizza.  I would walk in -25f temperature and a blizzard to get this pizza.  If I moved from Huntsville Alabama I will come back not only for the pizza, but for the customer service.   They match the customers they serve.   Thank you!  Bravo!
Food is delicious. I can’t comment on the table service or inside dining experience due to COVID-19 policies forcing take out service only.
Staff has a terrible attitude.  Incredibly rude.
It was great!!!!

The food was great, as always. One of the waiters acted like he wasn't happy with his job. ...like he was entitled to something that I was not able to offer him. Maybe he should just find a different job.

Husband and I each ordered pizzas. Food was average, nothing special and not worth the price. The worst part was waiting over 1.5hrs for that food, as part of a large group (14 people), and we made a reservation with their catering & events person two weeks in advance. So no excuse not to have enough staff (on a Sunday at 6:30. Not a typically busy time). While we were waiting and wondering about our food, waitress didn't keep drinks topped up or offer to check on our food. Several people in my group had something wrong with their order, including very undercooked doughy calzones. Manager came out after and offered discounts and made amends but that was after a train wreck of dinner plans.
The Greco pizza was terrific. So was the CA Pinot noir.
Good food, service was off and on
Delicious pasta and pizza!

My wife and I enjoyed a delicious dinner with great friends at Pane e Vino Pizzeria. I ordered the a pizza with goat cheese and my wife ordered a sandwich. The restuarant is conveniently located on the side of the museum in Huntville.
Went on a Friday lunch. Easy to find seating. Services as prompt and friendly. Ate Greek calzone. Best I have had in south. As good as I have eaten in NY.
The food was delicious.
Not great service or food
Imagine an Olive Garden, then forget everything you know about Olive Garden and replace that with your experience you will get here. Now you know Italian food. You're welcome.
Love the pizzas

Outstanding pizza and a decent wine list. Staff seemed to be going out of their way to not serve the two of us, though it didn't seem particularly busy. Good manager finally checked on us, apologized, comped our appetizer, and started waiting our table herself. Hopefully it was a fluke and the service improves, as the food was great and we'd like to come back.
The food is always great. They have a vanilla beer occasionally that I love, otherwise I default to wine. Service is always great :)
Great food and awesome service!!
Great food, so far we've only eaten here 3 times, but we will definitely continue to come back.
Great Pizza... the clemenza is very good.
Had a French 75 and a delicious calzone. Hadn't been there in a while but it seems they have kept up on their quality of drinks and menu items. The cheesy bread is also delicious. :)
Good pizza and drinks; very casual

It’s under new management and definitely not the same. This used to be my favorite restaurant. The manager was too busy socializing with friends and her employees constantly forgot multiple things I ordered. My daughters food came out when we were almost done eating. I waited for a glass of coke for 20 minutes. I asked for pulled pork on my pizza and there was LITERALLY 2 pieces. I would’ve ordered a cheese pizza and they had the nerve to charge 1.50 extra for that poor excuse of pulled pork. I paid over $100 on a tab of not the best food, waiting for drinks and poor management and staff. I paid my bill and still left a tip, took that loss and won’t be back. I wish I could get my money back and put it to better use. Multiple people walked out yesterday before we even got our food , I don’t blame them.

Amazing food all around. The staff is hit or miss when it comes them either being nice or rude. Also not the most polite people when trying to call in a to-go order! The rating is strictly because of staff.
Always a great place to eat when enjoying a stroll around Big Spring

Truly outstanding pizza and a very cool location. If you are staying nearby, take the opportunity to walk through the park to get there. Only thing preventing me from rating five stars is that the bill was expensive.
Gluten 👏 Free 👏 Pizza
Good pizza. It's always busy!

Excellent!!!  Did not want to try this place. I figured it would be like other create your own pizza places-nasty.  It was nearly empty when we went in and the employees didnt seem interested in the few customers that were there. No one greeted us when we walked in and I didnt know we could seat ourselves.  They have a variety of paninis, pasta dishes, calzones, and pizza on the menu. Some pizzas are named with preset ingredients ($11-15).  you can create your own as well (base $11 and $1.50 each additional topping)The menu states gluten free options available for calzones and pizza. I do not know if its gluten free or if cross contamination could happen in the kitchen. You can see the guys prepping the pizza crusts in the back which was curious. I ordered a named pizza and adjusted the toppings a little ($11). I also ordered a half house salad ($4)  and a sparkling pomerita ($9)  The kids got a cheese pizza and drink for $7.  The pizza was delicious and perfectly done. It was about the size of a 10 inch dinner plate, even the kid pizza. It was served hot from the oven and was still hot after 10 minutes. The crust was perfectly done. Crisp to bite and slightly chewy. I will definitely make another stop here when I'm back in Huntsville. My kids said they want to make it a tradition to visit before their annual gymnastics comeptition. Dont judge a book by its cover on this one!

Delicious fresh pizza. Also had tiramisu at the servers recommendation and it was delicious. Server was friendly.  There weren't any other when I arrived (had an early dinner) it was refreshing to see deep cleaning going on in the kitchen.

Artisan pizza joint below the Art Museum. Fantastic crust. Sauce and toppings standard fare but delicious. Salad was good but a tad excess with dressing. Service was good but got a blank look when I was asked if we had reservations and I said no. We were asked to sit at the bar despite the restaurant remaining 50% full the entire meal.

The food was all around okay. Wasn't anything to gawk at. Their whiskey/scotch/bourbon selection was slim with mostly mid to lower shelf and a couple good mid-top shelf choices. I'd definitely go again to make sure my experience wasn't a one off, but I haven't had the opportunity yet.
This is by far my favorite pizza place in Alabama. Great atmosphere, heated patio, friendly staff, delicious food - this place has it all. Great for a quick lunch or a romantic meal.

What a great atmosphere! There was a wonderful live musician playing, and the wine prices are great. Once the food arrived, we were very impressed. I had the three cheese ravioli, and my husband had the spaghetti and meatballs. for the quality of the food and the view and everything else including the service, this is a great place to dine!

Pricey! Good food, was not very impressed with the service we received. A party of three after the anime convention at Von Braun. For the price and style of restaurant I expected better service.. the pizza was good though. We got a split pizza, one side I believe was pepperoni and the other was the mona lisa signature pizza.
My waitress (Kylee) was spot on.
Amazing food and service!
A good place to eat for pretentious yuppies. Pizza is not real pizza, caprese salad looked pretty but was not a traditional caprese salad. You would do better at Olive Garden...
Great service,  great pizza.
Good food at s decent price.
Yummy
The pizza was delicious. The location overlooking a small Lake was beautiful. The service was terrible the worst I've ever had
This place has gone downhill since it opened, but still pretty good pizza.

Having had celiac for 10 years I've eaten a lot of gluten free pizzas. This place legitimately has the BEST gluten free pizza I've ever had. I got the El Greco. I asked about separate prep, and they do a good job. I personally did not have a reaction.

Our group of 6 had a reservation for 6:15. We showed up on-time and were told there were no tables available for our group. There were two other tables with menus and utensils laid out for 6:30 reservations. The table we were slated for still had 2 people sitting down, eating their meal. It was a 4-top and we were a group of 6. None of it made sense, and despite our persistence, no headway was made. So they were able to reserve a specific table for some groups but not for all. The manager was not helpful and her responses to my wife were quite rude. We waited around for 15 minutes while other large parties were seated. After waiting, we made a phone call to another restaurant and left. The managers response and the staff’s inability to hold the reservation, which truly is the most important part of the reservation, was enough for me to cross this one off our list for good.
Can’t even eat the food if they don’t actually honor your reservation when you call ahead

Staff was rude.  It was like pulling teeth to have them smile.  They did not greet me when I walked in.  I asked a question about the museum.  They were not helpful and  in fact after I asked my question a staff member said to not answer questions to me.  As someone visiting I found their behavior and demeanor to be rude and unwelcoming.  It’s too bad because everywhere I have visited in my short time in Huntsville people have been amazingly warm, welcoming and open to sharing the best that the city has to offer.  When I return I will go back to those places but NOT Pane E Vino... accept to use the bathroom.
Setting is beautiful and food is fantastic.
Food and atmosphere was great. Very nice view of the park if you're sitting outside!!!
Great place for a casual bite. Decent service. Try the butternut squash ravioli!
Good was great.  Service was super slow.  I really think they forgot about us. We were there over 1.5 hours, 3 people.  We had a pizza, calzone and ravioli.   Tasted good.

Best wait staff service I have experienced in a very long time. The young gentleman that waited on our wedding party did an outstanding job. The good was also very good. The location was nice right next to the city park. The biggest downside was the lack of parking. We parked in the museum parking after hours and it was not a problem. I'd go back.
Place is great but the big screen TV is out of place for the environment.
Great selection of menu and the food was very good. The staff was also very nice.

Delicious food and drinks! Their weekly trivia night on Tuesdays is great! Their outdoor seating is good and their bar/restaurant atmosphere is very nice. It has both fine dining and a quick bite vibe.

The flavor profile was good....but...the crust on my Mona Lisa was day old and the toppings were just laying on the crust.   There was no sauce to hold the "cold" toppings on my pizza and no cheese to bind everything together.     Nothing was "baked together".    I scraped off the toppings like I would scrape them off cardboard and tried to eat them like a salad...not successful.    Beautiful view of the pond...the only reason I enjoyed my visit.  (Oh,  the waitress was wonderful)

Service was EXTREMELY slow. Took over 30 minutes to get our food. We didn’t order anything that required much prep after watching how the kitchen staff prepares the food. The people in the kitchen aren’t the most hygienic as I watched multiple times the prep chefs touching their faces and heads and then plating food with their hands wearing no gloves. The food itself is reminiscent of a microwave Italian TV dinner. I would not recommend.

From our time of order, our food took about 45 minutes or more to come out which seemed long for our party of two. I will say the place was relatively busy on Thursday night, so we gave them some credit there.  I had the salvador dali pizza and my wife had the chicken alfredo. My pizza was ok and was not anything special. The pizza tasted plain and as if there wasn't a lot of effort put into making it. The chicken alfredo came out cold and the chicken was not cooked all the way as if they pieces were pulled out of the freezer and were not thawed during the cooking process. The reason I give two stars instead of one is because the manager took the chicken alfredo off our bill. Nonetheless, we left Pane E Vino very unsatisfied and disappointed.

Such a beautiful little treasure! At the heart of Huntsville's downtown Big Spring Park, and in the Huntsville Museum of Art building sits my favorite Italian restaurant! We sat on the outdoor patio, listening to live music and enjoying handmade pasta creations while the kids played in the park.  From traditional pizza, calzone and panini to mushroom and butternut squash raviolis! This place has something beautiful for everyone!

Went to this location and informed the server we're vegan so we can't have dairy, egg, or meat so we asked about the marinated olives and she said that'd be fine but when we asked about what else we could have she said she wasn't sure because the bread had egg in it. When our order came out it came with bread so we asked if we could have it and she had to go make sure again and came back with an "I don't know because it comes from somewhere else" so we just had to send the dish back. Assuming no vegan options here since they don't know what's in their food...

We weren't expecting to eat anywhere as we were walking around Big Spring Park, but the kids became thirsty.  A gentleman named Aaron(sp?) approached us playing Pokemon Go and we mentioned we were thirsty and asked for a place to get drinks. He then told us he was the kitchen manager and was extremely helpful and assisted in getting the kids drinks.  The helpfulness and enthusiasm is unprecedented, and we are extremely grateful.  Definitely will stop in whenever we are by because of this act alone. Thank you to all the staff for the hospitality shown. The antipasti platter is divine as well!
Lovely place, great food, friendly service
A little pricey, but totally worth it.  The service was excellent and the food was delicious.  I'll eat here again :)

Make sure you make a reservation! Waited an hour for a table without a reservation, but it was worth the wait. Service was a bit slow, but they were slammed and we weren't in a rush. Food was GREAT and they also have great drinks. Drinks pictured on the right side of the pic are the Italian Margarita (orange) and the clear skies (clear). Meal pictured is the chicken carbonara pasta, which was great! Will definitely return to Pane E Vino as long as I dont have a time constraint!

We went to take a walk around the park and decided to try them and was very happy we did food was excellent as was the service and we will definitely return again.
